  Domain: mathematics
  ID: opa.mathematics.homological-algebra.generating-hypothesis
  Status: Open

  In stable homotopy theory, we study spaces "up to suspension." The generating hypothesis says that stable homotopy groups detect everything: if a map between finite spaces induces the zero map on all stable homotopy groups, then the map itself must be zero (stably).

